comment: Caldwell-Pope (DET) makes contact with Adams (OKC) that affects his ability to set the screen.
Westbrook (OKC) is correctly called for a foul on Drummond (DET) but an away-from-the-play foul should be called.
Baynes (DET) sets the screen on Westbrook (OKC) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
Adams (OKC) sets the screen on Caldwell-Pope (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
[Detectable with stop watch] Drummond (DET) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Westbrook (OKC) establishes a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact from Jackson (DET).
Adams (OKC) sets the screen on Caldwell-Pope (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Jackson (DET) makes incidental contact with Foye (OKC) while jumping to knock away the pass.
Kanter (OKC) pushes Baynes (DET) and affects his ability to maintain a legal guarding position contesting Foye's (OKC) driving shot attempt.
Adams (OKC) sets the screen on Tolliver (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
LHH shows that Waiters (OKC) makes contact with Jackson's (DET) waist that affects his RSBQ and causes him to step OOB.
Westbrook (OKC) commits a take foul on Jackson (DET).
[Incidental or immaterial] Waiters (OKC) briefly engages with Caldwell-Pope (DET).
Adams (OKC) commits a take foul on Baynes (DET).
